    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-06-13T11:39:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-06-13T11:39:00-05:00" n="230"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d230">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">795.00/6–1354: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">United States Delegation</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret<lb/>
                            <gloss target="#t_niact1">niact</gloss>
                        </hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-06-13T12:39:00-04:00"
                            >June 13, 1954—12:39 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Tosec1">Tosec</gloss> 411. Geneva’s <gloss target="#t_Secto1"
                        >Secto</gloss> 431 repeated Seoul 124 Tokyo 130.<note n="1" xml:id="d230fn1"
                        >Dated June 12. <ref target="#pg_369">p. 369</ref>.</note> Tokyo also pass
                        <gloss target="#t_CINCUNC1">CINCUNC</gloss>. Secretary has not seen
                    reference telegram. Department believes it constitutes good basis for discussion
                    with other <pb facs="0397" n="371" xml:id="pg_371"/> delegations. <persName
                        corresp="#p_PYT1">Pyun</persName> may have trouble with undertaking
                    next-to-last paragraph make further efforts if Communists accept fundamental
                    principles but hope you can convince him.</p>
                <p>Since Communist proposals have paid lip service to “free elections”, suggest
                    might be clearer and more pointed revise last sentence second paragraph to read
                    “The Communist delegations fear and reject any elections conducted under
                    conditions of genuine freedom.”</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DJF1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Dulles</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
